  "response": "Opinions on Ben Affleck's acting vary, but some common criticisms include:\n\n1. Perceived lack of range\n- Often seen as wooden or emotionally unexpressive\n- Tends to play similar types of characters\n- Sometimes criticized for having a limited acting style\n\n2. Early career choices\n- Starred in several critically panned movies (like \"Gigli\")\n- Viewed as having more success as a director than an actor\n\n3. Wooden performance style\n- Sometimes considered stiff or unconvincing in dramatic roles\n- Accused of not fully embodying complex characters\n\n4. Overexposure in the late 1990s and early 2000s\n- Became somewhat of a pop culture target\n- Suffered from media overexposure and backlash\n\nHowever, many people also respect Affleck's work, particularly in films like:\n- \"Good Will Hunting\"\n- \"Argo\" (which he directed and starred in)\n- \"Gone Girl\"\n- \"The Town\"\n\nHis reputation has improved significantly in recent years, with critics acknowledging his growth as an actor and his strong directorial skills. Opinions remain mixed, but he's generally more respected now than in the early 2000s.",
